%N A274421 Decimal expansion of V_6, a Quantum Field Theory constant (negated) related to the coloring of the tetrahedron with six masses.
%D A274421 Jonathan Borwein and Peter Borwein, Experimental and Computational Mathematics: Selected Writings, Perfectly Scientific Press, 2010, p. 106.
%H A274421 David J. Broadhurst, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s100529900935">Massive 3-loop Feynman diagrams reducible to SC* primitives of algebras of the sixth root of unity</a>, The European Physical Journal C-Particles and Fields, Vol. 8, No. 2 (1999), pp. 311-333, p. 320; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/hep-th/9803091">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:hep-th/9803091, 1998, p. 18.
%F A274421 V6 = 6*zeta(3) - 13*zeta(4) - 8*U - 4*C^2, where U is A255685 and C is A143298.
%e A274421 -10.03527847976878917191470068515890023865033349600275134054452580...
%t A274421 C0 = A143298 = (9 - PolyGamma[1, 2/3] + PolyGamma[1, 4/3])/(4*Sqrt[3]);
%t A274421 U = A255685 = Pi^4/180 + (Pi^2/12)*Log[2]^2 - (1/12)*Log[2]^4 - 2*PolyLog[4, 1/2];
%t A274421 V6 = 6 Zeta[3] - 13 Zeta[4] - 8 U - 4 C0^2;
%t A274421 RealDigits[V6, 10, 101][[1]]
%o A274421 (PARI) 6*zeta(3) - 17*zeta(4) - 2*Pi^2*log(2)^2/3  + 2*log(2)^4/3 + 16*polylog(4, 1/2) - 4*(9 - psi'(2/3) + psi'(4/3))^2/48 \\ _Amiram Eldar_, Jul 05 2026
